The Final Flight (52.33 min)

British Airways retired it's Concorde on October 24, 2003, thus ending the era of Champagne and caviar at Mach 2 forever. For 27 years, Concorde carried about 4 million people and flew 50000 supersonic flights. This program takes viewers aboard one of Concorde's final flights to experience the thrill of supersonic travel.
